The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning and neural networks for communication, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on end-to-end learning and the use of neural networks suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve real robots, indicating that it may also fall under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of signals and representation of information suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of neural networks for learning suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
